Place a foil-lined #baking sheet{} on top rack (for 4 servings, 2 foil-lined sheets,
on top and middle racks) and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all
produce. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}(thinly sliced). Drain
@pineapple{4} over a #small bowl{}, reserving juice. Stir ¼ of the onion,
half the @red wine vinegar{5%tsp} (you'll use the rest later), and a pinch of
@salt{pinch} into #bowl{} with pineapple juice. Set aside.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in a large pan over medium heat.
Add remaining onion and cook, stirring and adding splashes of water as necessary
to prevent sticking, until softened, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve, core, and very thinly slice @poblano pepper{1}(thinly sliced) into
strips. Toss in a second small #bowl{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp},
@salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch}. Dice @fresh mozzarella{4}(diced into ½-inch pieces).
Finely chop @cilantro{1/4}(finely chopped) leaves and stems.

Once cooked onion is softened, increase heat under pan to medium high. Add
pineapple and another drizzle of oil; cook, stirring, until pineapple is lightly
browned, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in remaining vinegar. Cook, stirring, until
onion and pineapple are caramelized and jammy, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Turn off
heat and season with salt and pepper.

Brush or rub each side of @flatbread{2} with a drizzle of @olive oil{}. Remove
prepared baking sheet from oven; carefully place flatbreads on it (for 4 servings,
divide flatbreads between 2 prepared sheets). Evenly spread with @BBQ sauce{4},
then top with caramelized onion and pineapple, poblano, @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4}(shredded),
and mozzarella.

Return flatbreads to top rack until cheese has melted and edges are golden brown,
~{10-12%minutes}. (For 4 servings, return to top and middle racks; swap rack
positions halfway through baking.) Transfer to a #cutting board{} and top with
cilantro and pickled onion to taste. Slice into pieces and serve.

> Sweet and savory is a combo we can always get behind (for both dinner, dessert,
> and snacks—hello, Chicago-style popcorn). This ode to the dynamic flavor duo
> starts with a layer of BBQ sauce. The tangy-sweet condiment is spread on top of
> a golden, crispy crust, then piled with pickled and caramelized onions,
> poblano pepper, and, of course, juicy, lightly charred pineapple. Thought we
> forgot the cheese? Never. Melty mozzarella and Monterey Jack give you a cheese
> pull with every bite. Once you dig in, your taste buds will be lighting up.